HANOI, July 6 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam imported more than 3.7 million tons of plastic worth approximately 6.8 billion U.S. dollars in the first half of this year, up 0.9 percent in volume and 11.8 percent in value year on year, the Ministry of Industry and Trade said on Wednesday. Between January and June, the country spent nearly 4.2 billion dollars importing plastic products, up 5.7 percent from the same period last year, according to the ministry. In 2021, Vietnam imported over 6.9 million tons of plastic totaling more than 11.6 billion dollars, up 4.7 percent and 38.2 percent respectively from the previous year, according to the General Statistics Office.  â– 